Hi,

I want to introduce you to iCare, a start-up set to disrupt existing models of charitable donations and fundraising. iCare came about as a response to the inefficiencies and delays involved in charitable donations and disaster relief. For example, text-to-donate funds for Hurricane Sandy relief were delayed up to 90 days and had significant fees imposed. Relief aid, and more-over charitable donations in general, have reached over $320 billion annually in the US alone. Many of these donations are made on impulse, and donors dont read the fine print. This problem affects a lot of people, a lot of non-profit organizations, and a lot of money.

iCare solves this problem by using innovative mobile applications that facilitate instant, secure donations with automated record keeping. Through a strong partnership with PayPal, all of the money is handled transparently and securely. iCare does it in a way that is fun and engaging for donors, allowing them to create their own videos and crowd-fundraising campaigns for the non-profit organization of their choice. The user generated fundraising campaigns and involvement make iCare viral in nature and builds user loyalty.

Whats really exciting is how the non-profit organizations have reacted. We have formed an array of strong partnerships with both local and national non-profit organizations, such as Dress for Success, the Girl Scouts of Texas, the Texas Association of Non-Profit Organizations, and bands such as Of Monsters and Men and The Used. We have some great corporate partners as well, including PayPal and Vimeo. iCare currently supports over 6,000 of the largest charities in America. We are coordinating our launch campaign across these organizations and their existing media channels. Were thinking big, and that means we need funding to grow.

Our website is www.iCareCause.com
